Operations

TransducerCycleDataFields getFields()

Gets the fields of this TransducerCycleData object.

Return Value

TransducerCycleData object fields

void setFields(TransducerCycleDataFields fields, FieldNameList fieldNames)

Updates the fields of this TransducerCycleData object. If one or more fields are specified, only the fields listed will be updated, the other fields will be left unchanged. If the field list is empty ALL fields will be updated. The available fields are:

  • Transducer
  • Cycle
  • SoftwareScaling

Parameters

fields
updated fields structure
fieldNames
a string list with field names to be updated

Transducer* getTransducer()

Gets the proxy to the Transducer object refered to by the Transducer field.

Return Value

Transducer interface

Return Value
